HEADWORD: Forfete
<hw>For"fete</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Forfeit</er>.]</ety> <def>To incur a penalty; to transgress.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And all this suffered our Lord Jesus Christ that never
<qex>forfeted</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forfex</ent>⟦br⟧
